title: 3 Live Hits Of Chris De Burgh
description:
Chris de Burgh

      Genre(s)   Progressive rock, art rock, soft rock, pop rock, rock 

 Occupation(s)   Musician, singer-songwriter

 Years active    1974-Present


         Chris de Burgh (born Christopher John Davison on 15 October 1948) is an Irish-based musician and singer-songwriter who holds British nationality[1] . A musician who writes a variety of mixed instrumental material, Chris de Burgh had huge success in Ireland, Britain and the United States with the 1986 hit "The Lady in Red".

         Chris De Burgh's most famous song is "The Lady in Red" from the 1986 album Into the Light. That album also included the song "For Rosanna", written to celebrate the 1984 birth of his daughter Rosanna Davison, who would later go on to win the 'Miss World' title in 2003. He also has two sons named Hubie and Michael by his wife Diane
